spec_data.Name: perl-MooseX-StrictConstructor
spec_data.Description:
Simply loading this module makes your constructors "strict". If your
constructor is called with an attribute init argument that your class does
not declare, then it calls "Carp::confess()". This is a great way to catch
small typos.
spec_data.Signature: RSA/SHA256, Fri 28 Jul 2017 02:02:05 PM EDT, Key ID f55e7430f5282ee4
spec_data.Summary: Make your object constructors blow up on unknown attributes
